#Titania_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.216923552443255,80,"Now I perceive they have conjoined all three To fashion this false sport in spite of me.","The nine-men's-morris is filled up with mud, And the quaint mazes in the wanton green, For lack of tread, are undistinguishable.";;
#Titania_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.228985296121914,39,"Bootless speed When cowardice pursues and valor flies!","These are the forgeries of jealousy;" And never
column7: By pavèd fountain or by rushy brook
column8: Or in the beachèd margent of the sea
column9: To dance our ringlets to the whistling wind
column10: But with thy brawls thou hast disturbed our sport.""";

column1: #Titania_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.231239466041567,93,"This you should pity rather than despise.","But she, being mortal, of that boy did die, And for her sake do I rear up her boy, And for her sake I will not part with him.";;
#Titania_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.242548633046168,79,"Lo, she is one of this confederacy!","Then I must be thy lady.";;

#Titania_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.255256956783507,25,"You draw me, you hard-hearted adamant!","Why art thou here, Come from the farthest steep of India, But that, forsooth, the bouncing Amazon, Your buskined mistress and your warrior love, To Theseus must be wedded, and you come To give their bed joy and prosperity?";;
#Titania_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.257793088190013,55,"I see no blood, no wound.","The fold stands empty in the drownèd field, And crows are fatted with the murrain flock.";;
#Titania_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.258428115548974,112,"You see how simple and how fond I am.","Be kind and courteous to this gentleman.";;

#Titania_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.259422497150563,90,"Wherefore speaks he this To her he hates?","The moon, methinks, looks with a wat'ry eye, And when she weeps, weeps every little flower, Lamenting some enforcèd chastity.";;
#Titania_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.263180133075029,26,"But yet you draw not iron, for my heart Is true as steel.","Set your heart at rest: The Fairyland buys not the child of me.";;

#Titania_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.26476944724854,83,"All schooldays' friendship, childhood innocence?","The spring, the summer, The childing autumn, angry winter, change Their wonted liveries, and the mazèd world By their increase now knows not which is which.";;
#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.211382227832398,95,"This sport, well carried, shall be chronicled.","Lysander and myself will fly this place.";;
#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.222558706659614,80,"Now I perceive they have conjoined all three To fashion this false sport in spite of me.","Tell true, even for my sake!";;
#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.243430030071741,43,"We should be wooed and were not made to woo.","Too high to be enthralled to low.";;

#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.252133639720846,70,"Nor none, in my mind, now you give her o'er.","I know not by what power I am made bold, Nor how it may concern my modesty In such a presence here to plead my thoughts;" But I beseech your Grace that I may know The worst that may befall me in this case If I refuse to wed Demetrius.""";
#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.262723787179127,26,"But yet you draw not iron, for my heart Is true as steel.","Take comfort: he no more shall see my face.";;
#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.263789625566489,67,"Will you give her o'er?","Ah, good Demetrius, wilt thou give him me?";;
#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.267283228395783,79,"Lo, she is one of this confederacy!","What a dream was here!";;

#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.269591694576883,88,"Our sex, as well as I, may chide you for it, Though I alone do feel the injury.","I know not by what power I am made bold, Nor how it may concern my modesty In such a presence here to plead my thoughts;" But I beseech your Grace that I may know The worst that may befall me in this case If I refuse to wed Demetrius.""";
#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.273892181245747,78,"Never did mockers waste more idle breath.","An adder did it, for with doubler tongue Than thine, thou serpent, never adder stung.";;
#Hermia_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.274247586205821,116,"I will not trust you, I, Nor longer stay in your curst company.","You, mistress, all this coil is long of you.";;
#Lysander_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.195112076814603,78,"Never did mockers waste more idle breath.","I had no judgment when to her I swore.";;
#Lysander_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.210152892387909,35,"Nor doth this wood lack worlds of company, For you, in my respect, are all the world.","Or else misgraffèd in respect of years -";;

#Lysander_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.23004170833231,95,"This sport, well carried, shall be chronicled.","And touching now the point of human skill, Reason becomes the marshal to my will And leads me to your eyes, where I o'erlook Love's stories written in love's richest book.";;

#Lysander_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.233264165979362,80,"Now I perceive they have conjoined all three To fashion this false sport in spite of me.","I mean that my heart unto yours is knit, So that but one heart we can make of it;" Two bosoms interchainèd with an oath -  So then two bosoms and a single troth.""";
#Lysander_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.250140257327054,43,"We should be wooed and were not made to woo.","Or else misgraffèd in respect of years -";;

#Lysander_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.262352780433511,25,"You draw me, you hard-hearted adamant!","My love is more than his; My fortunes every way as fairly ranked (If not with vantage) as Demetrius';" And (which is more than all these boasts can be) I am beloved of beauteous Hermia."""

#Lysander_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.263293622677183,116,"I will not trust you, I, Nor longer stay in your curst company.","I swear by that which I will lose for thee, To prove him false that says I love thee not.";;

#Lysander_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.269165001245243,36,"Then, how can it be said I am alone When all the world is here to look on me?","Or, if there were a sympathy in choice, War, death, or sickness did lay siege to it, Making it momentany as a sound, Swift as a shadow, short as any dream, Brief as the lightning in the collied night, That, in a spleen, unfolds both heaven and Earth, And, ere a man hath power to say “Behold!” The jaws of darkness do devour it up.";;
#Lysander_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.269480034474225,12,"He will not know what all but he do know.","As you on him, Demetrius dote on you!";;
#Lysander_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.280489151740477,9,"Would that fault were mine!","Why should not I then prosecute my right?";;
#Demetrius_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.0784904363601399,12,"He will not know what all but he do know.","Relent, sweet Hermia, and, Lysander, yield Thy crazèd title to my certain right.";;
#Demetrius_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.127712000652272,8,"The more I love, the more he hateth me.","Relent, sweet Hermia, and, Lysander, yield Thy crazèd title to my certain right.";;
#Demetrius_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.172605624151925,83,"All schooldays' friendship, childhood innocence?","You spend your passion on a misprised mood.";;

#Demetrius_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.185764470445158,19,"As waggish boys in game themselves forswear, So the boy Love is perjured everywhere.","Relent, sweet Hermia, and, Lysander, yield Thy crazèd title to my certain right.";;

#Demetrius_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.186261793573538,80,"Now I perceive they have conjoined all three To fashion this false sport in spite of me.","So should the murdered look, and so should I, Pierced through the heart with your stern cruelty.";;
#Demetrius_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.186574436619814,22,"Then to the wood will he tomorrow night Pursue her.","Relent, sweet Hermia, and, Lysander, yield Thy crazèd title to my certain right.";;
#Demetrius_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.192505750227854,95,"This sport, well carried, shall be chronicled.","Here, therefore, for a while I will remain.";;
#Demetrius_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.194622110197309,3,"My ear should catch your voice, my eye your eye;" My tongue should catch your tongue's sweet melody.""
column6: yield Thy crazèd title to my certain right.""";

column1: #Demetrius_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.205288296622789,16,"Nor hath Love's mind of any judgment taste.","Relent, sweet Hermia, and, Lysander, yield Thy crazèd title to my certain right.";;

#Bottom_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.227742679258864,35,"Nor doth this wood lack worlds of company, For you, in my respect, are all the world.","And Phibbus' car Shall shine from far And make and mar The foolish Fates.";;
#Bottom_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.243701946390576,51,"If so, my eyes are oftener washed than hers.","Thy Thisbe dear and lady dear!”";;
#Bottom_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.24769275561229,95,"This sport, well carried, shall be chronicled.","Well, I will undertake it.";;
#Bottom_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.254268020014203,50,"How came her eyes so bright?","Thy Thisbe dear and lady dear!”";;
#Bottom_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.266913660891088,103,"I was never curst;" I have no gift at all in shrewishness.""
#Bottom_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.271199511817698,107,"Good Hermia, do not be so bitter with me.","If you think I come hither as a lion, it were pity of my life.";;

#Bottom_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.271594847328769,69,"Your vows to her and me, put in two scales, Will even weigh, and both as light as tales.","Good Master Peaseblossom, I shall desire you of more acquaintance too.";;
#Bottom_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.276049279346279,25,"You draw me, you hard-hearted adamant!","This is Ercles' vein, a tyrant's vein.";;
#Bottom_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.282132568129352,80,"Now I perceive they have conjoined all three To fashion this false sport in spite of me.","Now name the rest of the players.";;
#Bottom_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.282751513622743,88,"Our sex, as well as I, may chide you for it, Though I alone do feel the injury.","Well, I will undertake it.";;

#RobinGoodfellow_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.221405838585051,26,"But yet you draw not iron, for my heart Is true as steel.","But she perforce withholds the lovèd boy, Crowns him with flowers and makes him all her joy.";;

#RobinGoodfellow_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.226267175042274,43,"We should be wooed and were not made to woo.","I jest to Oberon and make him smile When I a fat and bean-fed horse beguile, Neighing in likeness of a filly foal.";;
#RobinGoodfellow_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.229489492633345,107,"Good Hermia, do not be so bitter with me.","I led them on in this distracted fear And left sweet Pyramus translated there.";;
#RobinGoodfellow_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.231351402167846,116,"I will not trust you, I, Nor longer stay in your curst company.","Your servant shall do so.";;
#RobinGoodfellow_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.239569420408355,88,"Our sex, as well as I, may chide you for it, Though I alone do feel the injury.","That must needs be sport alone.";;
#RobinGoodfellow_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.241264995119704,118,"My legs are longer though, to run away.","Your servant shall do so.";;
#RobinGoodfellow_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.248147408556542,36,"Then, how can it be said I am alone When all the world is here to look on me?","I am that merry wanderer of the night.";;
#RobinGoodfellow_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.249016759375638,25,"You draw me, you hard-hearted adamant!","I'll put a girdle round about the Earth In forty minutes.";;

#RobinGoodfellow_MND,"#Helena_MND",0.251656467044064,41,"Your wrongs do set a scandal on my sex.","And sometime lurk I in a gossip's bowl In very likeness of a roasted crab, And, when she drinks, against her lips I bob And on her withered dewlap pour the ale.";;
